The number of confirmed cases of coronavirus in Nigeria has risen to 81, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control said on Friday night. The NCDC confirmed 11 new cases. Eight of the cases were discovered in Lagos, while  two were discovered in Enugu and one in Edo State. “As at 11:55pm 27th March, there are 81 confirmed cases of  #COVID19 reported in Nigeria. 3 have been discharged with 1 death,” NCDC tweeted. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .